description:
&lt;p&gt;Norfolk and Norwich University Hospital NHS Foundation Trust is seeking to recruit an experienced Performance and Delivery Manager who will work within the Medicine Division. The role will be part of the Medicine Business Team, which supports the Division in service development, cost improvement, performance management and capacity planning.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Division has a budget in excess of £200 million, employs a workforce of over 2,500 staff and is committed to continuous improvement of services to provide great care for patients and their families. The Medicine Division provides services in both an inpatient and outpatient setting across a variety of specialties and manages a number of patient pathways which cover diagnostic, treatment, therapeutic and cancer.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This new post forms part of a re-structure that has recently taken place within the Medicine Divisional Management team, where a need was identified for more business support across the Division. As a Performance and Delivery Manager you will work closely with senior operational managers within Medicine at a tactical level to ensure the Division is achieving expected levels of performance across all key areas.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a truly exciting time of change to support us in the delivery of world class care for our patients. The Trust has recently moved out of special measures and one aspect of Medicine, our Palliative care services, has recently been awarded Outstanding and that is our ambition for the rest of the Division.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;It is a really exciting time to join the Medicine division; if you’re driven, ambitious and looking for a new challenge, apply today!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants will require exceptional leadership qualities, a commercial acumen, strong relationship management skills, a strong business understanding and credibility. You will be passionate about improvement and influencing change, you will be a natural leader who will facilitate and support collaborative working both internally and externally to the Trust, to ensure the delivery of high quality patient care. Experience of system working, primary and community care is highly desirable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be able to demonstrate excellent understanding of the acute hospital system, performance and quality standards. You will have expertise of managing performance (at both a service and Divisional level) in a provider setting. The successful candidate will be a motivated individual with highly developed influencing and negotiating skills in order to support the Division to achieve the highest standards in all aspects of its performance which will subsequently improve our patients’ outcomes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Full time:&lt;/strong&gt; 37.5 hours per week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview date: 12th November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Open for applications:&lt;/strong&gt; 29th October 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Close for applications:&lt;/strong&gt; 8th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Will Brown - Senior Business Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tel:&lt;/strong&gt; 01603 647233&lt;/p&gt;
